    <briefdescription>
<para>Optional 2-state (or N-state) flag tape — hemisphere N/S · E/W, or a mode letter. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>OFF by default (<computeroutput>enabled</computeroutput> = false). Position is configurable (not hardcoded rightmost). Populate <computeroutput>address</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>mask</computeroutput> from the A4EC constants. For a whole-word source (mask 0xFFFF) the value maps to a face by round(value/65535·(nFaces−1)); for a bit-packed source the masked value selects face 0 (zero) or the last face (non-zero). Bench-confirm the real encoding before trusting it. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
